article.headline: Idaho St. 75, Carroll, Mont. 74
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP)-Freshman Austin Kilpatrick scored 15 points and David Schroeder added 14 points and five rebounds to help Idaho State beat Carroll College 75-74 on Wedneday night Carroll (6-4), an NAIA school, took a 73-72 lead on a layup by Eric Henkel with 1:26 left. Idaho State (2-4) went up 75-73 on a three-point play by John Ofoegbu with 1:01 remaining. Henkel was fouled while shooting a 3-pointer with 0.2 seconds, but he made just one of three free throws and ISU held on for the win. Henkel led Carroll with 20 points and four assists, while Dallas Leslie added 18 points. Carroll, playing an exhibition game, shot 60 percent from the field, was 9-of-14 from 3-point range, outrebounded the Bengals 17-7 and held them scoreless for seven minutes while building a 45-35 halftime lead. Idaho State stormed back in the second half, using a 10-3 run in the first four minutes to pull to 48-45. A 3-pointer by ISU's Akbar Abdul-Ahad tied the score at 53, and sparked a 10-2 run that saw the Bengals open a 63-55 lead.
